# Bug 6 — monthly filter added to /api/v1/dashboard/summary
# Endpoint now accepts optional month & year query params. UI passes them from the new <input type="month">.
# UTC month boundaries for now — tz-correct boundaries come with Bug 4.

## prop-001 / tenant-a, no month (all-time, backward-compat)
{"property_id":"prop-001","total_revenue":2250.0,"currency":"USD","reservations_count":4,"month":null,"year":null}

## prop-001 / tenant-a, March 2024 (UTC boundaries)
## — res-tz-1 (2024-02-29 23:30 UTC) is CURRENTLY excluded, see Bug 4 next
{"property_id":"prop-001","total_revenue":1000.0,"currency":"USD","reservations_count":3,"month":3,"year":2024}

## prop-001 / tenant-a, February 2024 (UTC boundaries) — res-tz-1 currently lands here
{"property_id":"prop-001","total_revenue":1250.0,"currency":"USD","reservations_count":1,"month":2,"year":2024}

## April 2024 — no reservations
{"property_id":"prop-001","total_revenue":0.0,"currency":"USD","reservations_count":0,"month":4,"year":2024}

## Half-specified param → 400
{"detail":"`month` and `year` must be provided together (or both omitted for all-time)."}

